kuatunensis
//Wittm.”, [p] “Naturhistorisches// Museum Basel // Coll. W. Wittmer ”, [p]“ CANTHARIDAE // CANTH00002946”; NHMB .

AEDEAGUS (
Fig. 5D‒F
). Strongly swollen dorsally in basal part, contracted in diameter basally; basal piece obviously shorter than dorsal plate of each paramere, with a large, bifurcate conjoint middle nodule at base of ventral side; ventral process of each paramere nearly parallel to one another, long and flattened, apex rounded; dorsal plate slightly shorter than ventral process, nearly parallel-sided, layered in middle, external layer roundly emarginate in middle, internal layer feebly emarginate, apex subrounded; apical parts of laterophyses compressed and next to each other in middle, apex rounded and obviously exceeding middle emargination between dorsal plates.

In the original publication (
Wittmer 1979
), the aedeagus of this species was illustrated only in ventral view; here, it is also illustrated in dorsal and lateral views.
